Kingdoms.

Kingdoms are player-ruled realms. Each kingdom has a Ruler, a charter, a
roster of citizens, its own nobility titles, and a sigil carried by every
citizen.

Founding. New kingdoms are chartered and activated with the help of the
game administration. If you want a throne, speak with the admins.

Joining. Citizenship is by induction, in person. A noble with the power to
induct must stand in the same room as you and make the offer. You are then
asked whether you wish to become a citizen. Answer yes or no. You must be
at least level 5 and cannot already belong to another kingdom.

Citizenship. You carry your kingdom's sigil. It cannot be dropped, sold, or
stolen, and it marks you as a citizen to anyone who looks at you. You also
gain the kingdom channel. Type kchat followed by a message to speak to
every citizen. Type ekchat followed by a message to emote to them.

Nobility. The Ruler may create custom titles. Each title can grant any mix
of four powers: inducting members, removing members, assigning titles, and
owning a castle. New citizens start with the title Citizen. The title Ruler
is reserved for the kingdom's owner.

Management. The Ruler types managekingdom to open the management menu, the
Ministry of Administrative Affairs. The Deeds And Titles section sets and
views the charter, creates, edits, and removes titles, views citizens,
inducts new members, bestows titles, and strips citizenship. The Heraldry
And Propaganda section names the sigil, chooses its colors, and writes its
descriptions. The Castle Keep And Environs section is the office of the
Royal Engineer.

The whole kingdom hears arrivals and departures on the kingdom channel.

